cs.DC, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on Distributed Stream Data Processing Systems (DSDPSs) and proposes a novel control framework for scheduling in such systems. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the proposed framework uses Deep Reinforcement Learning (DRL) for control. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper proposes an AI-based approach for scheduling in DSDPSs. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a relevant category as the paper deals with control of a complex system (DSDPS) and proposes a control framework. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also possible as the proposed framework uses Deep Neural Networks for decision-making.
